-- Persian Gulf Stocks: Aldar, Ezdan, Sorouh and Raysut Cement
-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 2012-04-29T10:52:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/persian-gulf-stocks-aldar-emaar-ezdan-sorouh-raysut-cement.html
Abu Dhabi ’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  rose
for the fourth time in five days, gaining 0.2 percent to
2,512.17 at the 2 p.m. close in the emirate. The  DFM General
Index (DFMGI)  fell 0.8 percent.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)   advanced the most in more
than six weeks, gaining 4.4 percent to 1.18 dirhams. The Abu
Dhabi developer bailed out by the government last year said
first-quarter profit more than doubled to 478.2 million dirhams
($130 million).  Ezdan Real Estate Co. (ERES)   increased the most since
March 22, rising 2.1 percent to 19.4 riyals. The biggest Middle
East developer by market value said profit more than tripled to
144 million riyals ($40 million) as it gained from the sale of
property.  Sorouh Real Estate PJSC (SOROUH)   rose to the highest in
two weeks, climbing 1.8 percent to 1.15 dirhams. Abu Dhabi’s
second-biggest property developer by market value said first-
quarter profit climbed 30 percent as sales increased.  Raysut Cement Co. (RCCI)   surged the most since 2009,
rallying 7.1 percent to 1.122 rials. The largest Omani maker of
the building material by market value said first-quarter profit
climbed 37 percent as sales rose.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
